      "weather": "Fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Good little clash here, mainly between the Maher pair of SHOCKLETZ (7) and GILDED WATER (3). SHOCKLETZ was excellent first up in the Golden Mile at Bendigo, charging home for a narrow third after settling last. Bates gets in with 52kg after his valuable claim and with that run under the belt she might just be a bit fitter and sharper. GILDED WATER is the class resuming. He had a big spruik during the Spring as a possible Melbourne Cup horse, ultimately blowing up after bolting in the G3 Bart Cummings, run down in the Geelong Cup as favourite before a spell as well. He looked good winning a 1400m trial recently and may just be too strong. PUDDING (4) comes over from Adelaide in good form, making Arran Bay really stretch last time. 1800m is fine and he's rock hard fit. WONDER BOY (2) is flying but does meet SHOCKLETZ 7kg worse off from Bendigo, albeit he's won since. BANKERS CHOICE (1) next best back in trip.",
